{Peat}mossland,particularly Cadishead Moss,intensivley cultivated for {market-garden}crops such as (carrots, radish,lettuce,celery).Fertile, lowland area of small farm units that are well drained by ditches that lead into the{River Glaze}and then the{M'C {ship canal. }
{Rixton and Warburton}areas,have mixed soils of{peat,boulder clay}and {sand.Arable farming}is dominant,mainly winter{wheat,barley}plus potatoes.Farm units and field size is much larger.
The{sands and gravels}of{Red brook}and {River Glaze}are mainly devoted to {pastoral grassland.}
{Strawberries}are grown for self-picking by passing motorists on the loam soils of Mount Pleasant farm.
